 English many nouns can be singular or plural.";i:23;s:80:"Un homme one man deux hommes two men la chaise the chair les chaises the chairs.";i:24;s:130:"But there are quite a few French nouns that can only be singular sometimes because the noun has a different meaning in the plural.";i:25;s:211:"From middle english chayer chaire chaiere chaere chayre chayere from old french chaiere chaere from latin cathedra seat from ancient greek καθέδρα kathédra from κατά katá down ἕδρα hédra seat.";i:26;s:26:"A general word for a type.";i:27;s:35:"The plural form of chair is chairs.";i:28;s:30:"Chairs is the plural of chair.";i:29;s:125:"Many translated example sentences containing Chairperson French-English dictionary and search engine for French translations.";i:30;s:75:"Most French nouns form their plural by adding an -s to their singular form.";i:31;s:76:"If the singular noun ends in -s-x or -z no further-s is added in the plural.";i:32;s:57:"Most nouns ending in -eau or -eu add an -x in the plural.";i:33;s:72:"Most nouns ending in -ou take an -s in the plural with a few exceptions.";i:34;s:72:"If the singular noun ends in -al or -ail the plural usually ends in-aux.";i:35;s:72:"In French grammar heres how you turn a singular noun into a plural noun.";i:36;s:42:"Nouns that end in au take x in the plural.";i:37;s:82:"Bateau boat becomes bateaux boats and manteau overcoat becomes manteaux overcoats.";i:38;s:47:"Most nouns that end in ou take s in the plural.";i:39;s:102:"The most common rule for forming the plural of nouns and adjectives in French is actually very simple.";i:40;s:69:"Add a final -s in the spelling to mark a noun or adjective as plural.";i:41;s:134:"If you have a plural adjective followed by a plural noun then pronounce the final -s on the adjective if the noun begins with a vowel.";i:42;s:58:"This simply means that they are either SINGULAR or PLURAL.";i:43;s:77:"If there is only one noun substantif being talked about the noun is SINGULAR.";i:44;s:85:"If there is more than one noun substantif being talked about then the noun is PLURAL.";i:45;s:93:"Sometimes words in French have a change in spelling when they change from singular to plural.";i:46;s:168:"From Middle French chair char from Old French char charn earlier carn from Latin carnem accusative of carō from Proto-Italic karō from Proto-Indo-European ker- sker-.";i:47;s:39:"How to Know the Gender of French Nouns.";i:48;s:114:"A noun is a word that represents a person place or thing whether concrete eg chair dog or abstract idea happiness.";i:49;s:71:"In French all nouns have a genderthey are either masculine or feminine.";i:50;s:58:"Une banane a banana singular - des bananes bananas plural.";i:51;s:99:"The only thing that changed here except for the article more on the article here and here is the s.";i:52;s:85:"Ive added an s at the end of the word banane une chaise a chair - des chaises chairs.";i:53;s:21:"Nouns and adjectives.";i:54;s:24:"Formation of the plural.";i:55;s:41:"Nouns and adjective follow similar rules.";i:56;s:97:"Nouns and adjectives ending in -s -x or -z in the singular generally do not change in the plural.";i:57;s:15:"Le nez les nez.";i:58;s:52:"The most common way to form the plural is by adding.";i:59;s:16:"Chaire f plural.";i:60;s:67:"Chaires f I have held a chair at the same university for ten years.";i:61;s:60:"Joccupe une chaire dans la même université depuis dix ans.";i:62;s:16:"Siège m plural.";i:63;s:41:"Sièges m My office chair is comfortable.";i:64;s:37:"Mon siège de bureau est confortable.";i:65;s:40:"The plural form of chairman is chairmen.";i:66;s:301:"Another word for Opposite of Meaning of Rhymes with Sentences with Find word forms Translate from English Translate to English Words With Friends Scrabble Crossword Codeword Words starting with Words ending with Words containing exactly Words containing letters Pronounce Find conjugations Find names.";i:67;s:27:"How to say chair in French.";i:68;s:60:"If playback doesnt begin shortly try restarting your device.";i:69;s:88:"Videos you watch may be added to the TVs watch history and influence TV recommendations.";i:70;s:14:"To avoid this.";i:71;s:53:"Generally to form plurals you can follow these rules.";i:72;s:32:"Add an s to the end of the word.";i:73;s:94:"La chaiseles chaises the chairthe chairs Nouns ending in s x or z do not change in the plural.";i:74;s:108:"La sourisles souris the mousethe mice Nouns ending in al ail or au in the singular end in aux in the plural.";i:75;s:196:"Chair French Origin history From Middle French chair char from Old French char charn earlier carn from Latin carnem accusative of carō from Proto-Italic karō from Proto-Indo-European ker- sker-.";i:76;s:18:"Noun chair fem pl.";i:77;s:22:"Related words phrases.";}}